All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy) — stops one iteration early, skipping the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — iterates through all elements including the last
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition caused the loop to stop before reaching the final index, so the last item was never pushed into `results`. Removing it lets the loop run through the full array. ✅

